tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits, except for creatinine, which is at the upper limit of normal. Glycemic control (HbA1c, glucose) is adequate. Renal function and electrolytes are stable, but kidney function should be monitored due to borderline creatinine. No acute abnormalities detected.
